title: For Sale:  1911 Style 9 mm Star Super
postcontent:
Inspired by the famous 1911 Design: This is a beauty of a gun and “Classic” all the way: All steel construction that Star is famous for. Solidly built with a steel frame, slide and barrel. Completely of forged steel parts as it precedes the age of MIM. This gun represents the classic style of handguns with forged steel manufacturing, instead of stamped steel, alloy frames, plastic and polymer so common today.  This one is chambered for 9 mm like many Star pistols -- a little less recoil than the 45 ACP.
 
Performance and Handling: Recoil is light and still very controllable even with hot loads.   The weight soaks up what normally would be snappy recoil from a compact pistol. Love the accuracy and reliability shooting all kinds of ammo, JHP, etc.
 
 
Colt 1911 Commonalities:   The many similarities to the 1911 ACP make this pistol a favorite. First, the look and feel are squarely 1911. That very classic and natural pick up. Teed ramp design is the same as on the 1911.
 
 
Like the 1911, the Star using a Browning style lock up as is evidenced by the swinging link and locking lug on the barrel along with the removable barrel bushing.   
Action & Trigger: single-action with locked breech. Single action trigger break is excellent – very clean! Serrated finger pad for a sure grip.
 
 
PREMIUM FEATURES:
Checkering milled into the hammer for a sure feel.
Magazine well is beveled from the factory.
Throated from the factory.
Safeties: Thumb safety on left side like the Colt 1911. You can carry cocked and locked. Gun also has a Magazine Disconnect for additional safety.
Sights: notched rear blade and serrated front ramp. Easy to pick up at speed. The sight picture is easy to obtain in both slow and rapid-fire drills. The rear sight is drift adjustable for windage.
 
Grips: checkered brown
 
 Pivoting external claw extractor like the Browning Hi Power and other major semiautomatic brands.
Trigger has serrated finger pad.
Full-length guide rod with captive recoil spring.
Removable barrel bushing.
  
As a testament to their quality, Star firearms are still used by police, security and military agencies in Spain.   It reflects the reliability, durability and the quality of Spanish pistols and to the skill and workmanship of the workers of Star Firearms Bonifacio.
 
Conclusion:  The easy handling and resemblances to the classic Colt 1911 make this pistol a favorite among collectors, recreational shooters, or carry owners.

title: For Trade:  Taurus 44 Magnum
postcontent:
According to Buds - The Taurus Model 44 large frame revolver holds 6 rounds of full-power 44 Magnum loads. This revolver is hammer-forged for tough performance and confidence-boosting accuracy, and it comes with a hand-fitted action and a clean, crisp trigger right out of the box. The Model 44 features a ported barrel that reduces muzzle flip and felt-recoil, the Taurus Security System (TSS), and a transfer bar safety.
 Manufactured in 2011. I purchased this revolver in AZ and have enjoyed this revolver for 2 years but, think I'm getting over it. I havn't had any issues with the timing or cylinder lockup going out on me. The surface finish is a taurus surface finish so don't expect it to shine like a colt anaconda. It has wear on it and STILL looks good. This taurus is very accurate and has an excellent SA trigger....ok DA pull. The barrel porting does help with the recoil but so does weighing something like 45oz. I have Carried this revolver concealed for 2 winters and feel unstoppable when it's on me. this revolver is also extremly loud especially at an indoor range when the vectored muzzle blast reflects off the celing and resonates in your skull. I currently own S&W, Ruger, and Taurus revolvers and am a ruger fanboy when it comes to revolvers. With that said, Taurus REVOLVERS are still a great buy. with proper maintenence they should last forever.

It's a handsome pistol and if you're going to own a .380ACP, then Walther PPK would be the signature pistol to have. This is the same model pistol that James Bond carries in a lot of his movies. It is accurate, and a very manageable weight for a pocket .380, it is unfortunately two little for my large gorilla-hands.
